      en: ' - officially The EU will introduce the European Travel Information and Authorisation System (ETIAS), which will apply to citizens of countries that have visa-free travel with the EU. This is a new mandatory permit for short-term trips.\n\n‚ùì What is known:\n\n‚ñ´Ô∏èETIAS is not a visa, but a mandatory electronic authorization for entry into the EU.\n‚ñ´Ô∏èThe system covers 30 countries, including all Schengen zone states.\n‚ñ´Ô∏èApplication submission is online. This is a short questionnaire that can be filled out independently.\n‚ñ´Ô∏èCost is ‚Ç¨7. The authorization will be valid for 3 years or until the passport expires.\n‚ñ´Ô∏èObtaining a new passport will require a new ETIAS authorization.\n‚ñ´Ô∏èETIAS has not yet been launched. The start of operation is expected at the end of 2026.\n‚ñ´Ô∏èPersons with temporary protection in the EU will not need to go through ETIAS authorization. However, it will be necessary to confirm their status at the border.\n\nIn addition, from October 12, 2025, the EES (Entry/Exit System) will begin operating in the EU, which will replace manual passport stamping.\n\nüîó More information: <a href="https://travel-europe.europa.eu/etias_en?fbclid=IwY2xjawL4hc9leHRuA2FlbQIxMABicmlkETFmV1VWeUhveHpOV2xpd3E1AR43CvrD3-tOsvRZrgSOAy88unLdv9o3J2U1SSqFsVeX-u-sWpPZLIZccL860Q_aem_xjfs9jVUpNZyY7xnbGDSQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://travel-europe.europa.eu/etias_en</a>',
